      "text": "However, VitePress won't redirect <code>/</code> to <code>/en/</code> by default. You'll need to configure your server for that. For example, on Netlify, you can add a <code>docs/public/_redirects</code> file like this:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "<strong>Pro tip:</strong> If using the above approach, you can use <code>nf_lang</code> cookie to persist user's language choice:"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "RTL Support (Experimental) ​"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "For RTL support, specify <code>dir: 'rtl'</code> in config and use some RTLCSS PostCSS plugin like https://github.com/MohammadYounes/rtlcss, https://github.com/vkalinichev/postcss-rtl or https://github.com/elchininet/postcss-rtlcss. You'll need to configure your PostCSS plugin to use <code>:where([dir=\"ltr\"])</code> and <code>:where([dir=\"rtl\"])</code> as prefixes to prevent CSS specificity issues."
    },
